Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper deals with large-scale linear inverse problems and the trade-off between physical costs of the reconstruction process including computation time, communication loads, and the reconstruction quality. This is a core topic in information theory. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses the Bayesian framework and approximate message passing (AMP) algorithm, which are commonly used in machine learning. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper deals with multi-processor (MP) computational systems and lossily compressed messages, which are relevant to multimedia applications. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper deals with a multi-objective optimization problem (MOP) and the properties of the best trade-offs (Pareto optimality) in this MOP, which are relevant to systems and control. 
5. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper deals with communication loads and the trade-off between physical costs of the reconstruction process, which are relevant to networking and internet architecture.
